<h3>Elemental Silence</h3>

<p>A new concept for mages -- a mesmerize spell that works against summoned
beings (why does put so few summoned mobs in the game?).&nbsp; This spell will
only work on summoned beings up to level 60.&nbsp; It lasts 30 seconds.&nbsp; It
also has a memory blur component (30%).</p>

<h3>Black Steel</h3>

<p>A basic upgrade to our DD, but worth mentioning as it does 1400 damage.</p>

<h3>Blade of the Kedge</h3>

<p>Same as the previous 2 pet weapons, except this weapon's DD checks against
cold.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Child of Ro</h3>
<p>The new fire pet.&nbsp; VI has tuned fire pets at least twice now and still 
has it a bit off in my opinion.&nbsp; In the incarnation of Fire at this time, 
the pet casts several wizard spells, including the Old World favorite -- Ice 
Comet.&nbsp; Part of the design has lowered the melee skills of this pet 
significantly.&nbsp; It's interesting to have a wizard class pet...but sadly, 
the pet does not fight very intelligently.&nbsp; With a limited mana pool, the 
pet will often go OOM and resort to its poor melee abilities.&nbsp; At other 
times, the pet will randomly cast spells that might cause alarm...such as 
dispelling a DC.&nbsp; I'd like to see VI continue to improve this pet rather 
than return to the 49-and-under design for fire....but use it cautiously.</p>
<h3>Summon Jewelry Bag</h3>
<p>This spell will summon all 5 level 61 focus items.&nbsp; Be warned, the level
61 items are lore.&nbsp; Many a mage has crashed to the desktop summoning this
bag while wearing one of the focus items.&nbsp; In late August 2003, this spell
was improved to include the summoning of the DOT bracer.</p>
<h3>Other Upgrades</h3>
<p>A few upgrades this level are pretty important: <b>Malosinia</b> -- a debuff
upgrade and <b>Maelstrom</b><b> of Ro</b> -- a group version of Flameshield of
Ro (45 point DS).</p>
<p><i>Note: There was a rumor that went around after the PoP release that 
Maelstrom of Ro was not implemented.&nbsp; It is in the game...as a random award 
for a spectral parchment.</i></p>
